## Connecting the Printer to Raspberry pi using CUPS

Step 1: Set Up the Raspberry Pi

1. Download the Raspberry Pi OS image from the official website.

2. Use software like Raspberry Pi Imager to flash the OS onto a microSD card.

3. Insert the microSD card into the Raspberry Pi and power it on.

4. Follow the setup instructions to configure the Raspberry Pi.

Step 2: Install Printer Software

sudo apt update sudo apt install cups sudo usermod -aG lpadmin <Username>

Step 3: Configure CUPS 1. Open the CUPS interface by navigating to http://localhost:631 on your Raspberry Pi.

2. Connect Your Printer via USB to Rpi.

3. Add your printer through the CUPS interface.
